    <string name="how_to_read_map_title">How to read the Map</string>
    <string name="how_to_read_map_desc" formatted="false">Shows ECU fuel correction, not current rich/lean mixture.\n\nTrim = STFT + LTFT\n🟢 ±5% = Low learned correction\n🟡/🔴 Negative = ECU removing fuel\n🌐/🔵 Positive = ECU adding fuel\nA positive value does not mean the current AFR is lean while closed loop is correcting it. Measured Lambda (λ) appears inside mature cells when PID 01 34 is supported.\n\nPETROL stores the gasoline/E20 baseline. LPG/CNG stores the gas baseline.\nDEVIATION = LPG Trim - Petrol Trim.\nTUNE ASSIST uses that deviation as the gas multiplier direction: + add gas, - remove gas.\n\nCells with fewer than 3 stable hits remain neutral gray. Only compare maps collected with the same axis source.</string>
